  <Description>
    <Language>en</Language>
    <Type>General</Type>
    <Text>No swimming pool but suitable for budget travellers. This hotel also promotes environmental concerns - it is eco friendly by using compact fluorescent bulbs, air conditioning filters cleaned monthly, trees, etc. Moreover, the hotel also support a disabled artist with polio by helping him sell his oil paintings in the hotel. (12/07SW)</Text>
  </Description>
  <Description>
    <Language>en</Language>
    <Type>SurroundingArea</Type>
    <Text>Situated in old town Bangkok - and artistic and cosy place in the cultural centre of Bangkok. The hotel provides convenient access to cultural and historical attractions like the Wat Phra Kaew, Grand Palace, national museum, and Rajadamnoen Thai Boxing Stadium. In addition, the hotel is near the well-established traveller's community Khao San Road and Banglamphu shopping area.</Text>
  </Description>
  <Description>
    <Language>en</Language>
    <Type>RoomTypes</Type>
    <Text>Rooms with chic and contemporary Thai decor reflect art and culture. Each room is decorated with a different oil-painting showing cultural aspects. Also, guests can see more of the charm of old Bangkok while relaxing at the hotel. All rooms have air conditioning, with hot and cold shower, cable TV and Internet access. Bathroom is shower only.</Text>
  </Description>
  <Description>
    <Language>en</Language>
    <Type>PropertyInformation</Type>
    <Text>5-storey, white concrete and glass building.</Text>
  </Description>
  <Description>
    <Language>en</Language>
    <Type>DiningFacilities</Type>
    <Text>The restaurant serves international and Thai dishes for breakfast only.</Text>
